04/05/85 rebuild_pvolog

Syntax as a command:  rebuild_pvolog dvname {-control_args}


Function:  rebuilds a physical volume log by scanning all the volume
logs for instances of the dump volume specified.


Arguments:
dvname
   is the name of a dump volume.


Control arguments:
-brief, -bf
   specifies brief output.
-long, -lg
   specifies long output.
-working_dir -wd
   searches for the volume logs in the working directory; the resulting
   rebuilt physical volume log is placed in the directory [wd]>pvolog
   rather than the system default directories.
